The paper deals with meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Specifically, it proposes a new algorithm for model-agnostic meta-learning that is also distribution-agnostic. This makes it relevant to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category, as it is the primary subfield of machine learning and includes papers on meta-learning. The other categories are also relevant because the proposed algorithm can be applied to various tasks, including computer vision and control systems.
